quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  16,91,"And fulfill the covenant of Allāh when you have taken it, [O believers], and do not break oaths after their confirmation while you have made Allāh, over you, a security [i.e., witness]. Indeed, Allāh knows what you do."
  16,92,"And do not be like she who untwisted her spun thread after it was strong [by] taking your oaths as [means of] deceit between you because one community is more plentiful [in number or wealth] than another community.{1} Allāh only tries you thereby. And He will surely make clear to you on the Day of Resurrection that over which you used to differ.",1:[i.e., do not swear falsely or break a treaty or contract merely for a worldly advantage.]
  16,93,"And if Allāh had willed, He could have made you [of] one religion, but He sends astray whom He wills and guides whom He wills.{1} And you will surely be questioned about what you used to do.",1:[According to His knowledge of each soul's preference.]
  17,58,"And there is no city but that We will destroy it{1} before the Day of Resurrection or punish it with a severe punishment. That has ever been in the Register{2} inscribed.",1:[Because of the sins],2:[of its inhabitants.]
  17,59,"And nothing has prevented Us from sending signs [i.e., miracles] except that the former peoples denied them. And We gave Thamūd the she-camel as a visible sign, but they wronged her. And We send not the signs except as a warning."
  17,60,"And [remember, O Muḥammad], when We told you, ",1:[In His knowledge and power, meaning that Allāh would protect him (ﷺ) from their harm.],2:[During the miʿrāj (ascension) into the heavens.]
  18,25,"And they remained in their cave for three hundred years and exceeded by nine.{1}",1:[i.e., 309 lunar years.]
  18,26,"Say, "
  18,27,"And recite, [O Muḥammad], what has been revealed to you of the Book of your Lord. There is no changer of His words, and never will you find in other than Him a refuge."
